Step 1: Calculate the Return on Equity (ROE).  
• From the income statement, Net Profit = 963263.19  
• From the balance sheet, Total Owner's Equity = 13963263.19  
• ROE = (Net Profit / Owner's Equity) × 100  
  = (963263.19 / 13963263.19) × 100  
  ≈ 6.90%

Step 2: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
• From the balance sheet, Total Assets = 14930535.06  
• Liabilities = Total Assets – Owner's Equity = 14930535.06 – 13963263.19 = 967271.87  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 967271.87 / 14930535.06  
  ≈ 0.065

Step 3: Calculate the Gross Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 1713437.82  
• Total Revenue = 3025437.82  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1713437.82 / 3025437.82) × 100  
  ≈ 56.60%

Thus, the solution is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "6.90%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.065",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "56.60%"
  }
}
